## Installation

Steps to get the repo running locally (example):

```bash
python -m venv env
source env/bin/activate   # or .\env\Scripts\activate on Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt   # if exists
```

## Usage

Basic usage examples and quick commands:

- Run tests: `pytest -q`
- Run the local analysis helper (generates README):
